        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=2629&FORUM_ID=21&CAT_ID=7&Forum_Title=The+Haven+%2D+Albion+%26+General+Discussion+%2D+DAoC&Topic_Title=Layin%27+the+smack+down"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Well me, Aidem and Voltan decided to defend the realm with our newly pimped up and powerful level 20 destruction machines. Waplespunk couldn't join us he was busy starting some traveling circus in a foreign land. At first it was frustrating because we actually outnumbered the Middies but no one wanted to work together. Being the very capable whiners that we are we eventually formed a full group and headed out.</P><P>We were successful when the team worked as one and did keep them out or at the least kept them from rezzing their buddies. But it fell apart because way to many people have the Quake mentality and go for the quick easy kills. Way too many times the casters and healers were left unguarded to be taken out by stealth classes. It never fails the Mids would pop out and all of our guys would go running and leave us behind. Everyones eager to run after the easy kill but once the numbers increase they are all quick to say MEZ THEM Quick, Buff Me Please, Chain Cast Nuke. That got a bit annoying. </P><P>Nothing against you stealther guys but it seems like we had more stealthers than anything and about all they do is maybe give some intel every now and then but outside of that you never see them they just leech points of the rest of our kills. Wait till your in battle and maybe pop off a few critical hits every now and then if they are around. I understand you guys can't melee but come on I'm wearing armor thats made by Old Navy and carry a freaking stick. </P><P>Then there are the dillweeds that jump group for an easy kill and then come back and whine to get back in to leach everyone elses points. New rule if you jump group your gone forever unless you were taking a dump or something.</P><P>Ok well anyway enough of the rant I had alot of fun and am really looking forward to an all LOA group rather than pick up group. That could have been the problem. But I do see where alot of the complaints come from. </P><P>/Shane</P><P></P><P><BR></font></td>

